/etc/local.d/ — OpenRC drop-in scripts run at the `local` runlevel.

Every executable file in this directory ending in `.start` is run
after the default runlevel has finished starting (i.e. once the
system is up, before login banners appear).  Files ending in
`.stop` run at shutdown.  Anything else is ignored.

This is the right place for small per-host customisations that don't
warrant their own packaged init.d/<name> service:

  /etc/local.d/00-fix-foo.start    — fix up a quirk on this host
  /etc/local.d/load-some-modules.start
  /etc/local.d/wipe-stale-cache.stop

Files MUST be executable (chmod +x).  Order is alphabetical, so use
numeric prefixes (00-, 50-, 99-) to control sequence when it matters.

Logging: stdout/stderr is captured into /var/log/rc.log if
`rc_logger="YES"` in /etc/rc.conf.  Otherwise the output goes to the
console.

See `man 8 rc-local` for full details.  Per-package init.d scripts
under /etc/init.d/* should NOT live here — they belong in /etc/init.d/
proper with `rc-update add <name> default` to register.
